The second meeting of the Steering Committee of the Multi-agency Donor Coordination Platform for Ukraine was held, co-chaired by Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economics Mike Pyle, Finance Minister of Ukraine Sergii Marchenko, and European Commission Director-General for Neighborhood and Enlargement Negotiations Gert Jan Koopman. The meeting focused on coordinating economic support for Ukraine's financing needs and future economic recovery and reconstruction efforts. Ukraine outlined its early recovery priorities for 2023, including energy infrastructure, civilian demining, critical and social infrastructure, housing, and support for the private sector. They also provided an update on their reform agenda, supported by the recently approved IMF program, to pave the way for EU accession. Deputy National Security Advisor Pyle reaffirmed the United States' commitment to supporting Ukraine and ensuring effective oversight of funding. The Steering Committee will continue collaboration in the coming weeks, with the next meeting scheduled for May.